Class CountryModel

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.awt.Component
      • java.awt.Container

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.awt.image.ImageObserver, java.awt.ItemSelectable, java.awt.MenuContainer, java.io.Serializable, javax.accessibility.Accessible, javax.swing.SwingConstants
    public class CountryModel
extends javax.swing.JButton
    "CountryModel" represents a country's properties such as name, position, continent name that it belongs to, countries that it connected to, owner (player who owns it) name, Number of armies in, and color.
    Author:
    Suruthi
